26/08/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The association of Independent Trade Unions in BiH signed a collective agreement with representatives of public utilities in Sarajevo on Monday (25 August).
The contract regulates employee rights and obligations, as well as social protection mechanisms.
It also details the utilities' responsibilities in providing electricity, heating and water supplies, and various other services for the capital.
Cantonal Urban Planning and Environment Minister Zlatko Petrovic co-signed the document.
(Onasa - 25/08/03)
